## Branches — `<%= @project.full_path %>`

Manage repository branches for this project. All requests require a personal access token passed in the `PRIVATE-TOKEN` header.

**Base URL:** <%= request.base_url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>

**Authentication:**

```bash
curl <%= request.base_url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/repository/branches \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

---

### List Branches

```bash
curl "<%= request.base_url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/repository/branches" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

**Query parameters:**

- `search` (optional) — Filter branches by name (case-insensitive substring match)

**Response fields:**

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| `name` | Branch name |
| `default` | Whether this is the default branch |
| `protected` | Whether the branch is protected |
| `merged` | Whether the branch has been merged into the default branch |
| `state` | `active` or `stale` (inactive for more than 3 months) |
| `last_commit` | Object with the latest commit details |

**`last_commit` fields:**

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| `id` | Full commit SHA |
| `short_id` | Short commit SHA (8 chars) |
| `title` | First line of the commit message |
| `message` | Full commit message |
| `author_name` | Author name |
| `author_email` | Author email |
| `authored_date` | Date the commit was authored |
| `committed_date` | Date the commit was committed |
| `committer_name` | Committer name |
| `committer_email` | Committer email |

---

### Get a Single Branch

```bash
curl "<%= request.base_url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/repository/branches/:name" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

- `:name` — Branch name (URL-encoded if it contains slashes, e.g. `feature%2Fmy-branch`)

---

### Create a Branch

```bash
curl -X POST "<%= request.base_url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/repository/branches" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"branch": "my-new-branch", "ref": "main"}'
```

**Fields:**

- `branch` (required) — Name of the new branch
- `ref` (required) — Branch name or commit SHA to create the branch from

Returns the created branch with the same structure as **Get a Single Branch** (`201 Created`).

---

### Delete a Branch

```bash
curl -X DELETE "<%= request.base_url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/repository/branches/:name" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

- `:name` — Branch name (URL-encoded if it contains slashes)

Returns `204 No Content` on success. Returns `403 Forbidden` if the branch is protected or is the default branch.
